Definition.WordDefinition: unobjectionable adj 1: (of behavior or especially language) free from objectionable elements; fit for all observers; "good clean fun"; "a clean joke" [syn: {clean}] [ant: {dirty}] 2: not causing disapproval; "it was an innocuous remark"; "confined himself to innocuous generalities"; "unobjectionable behavior" [syn: {innocuous}] 3: not objectionable; "the ends are unobjectionable; it's the means that one can't accept"
